Package: home-automation
Version: 1.0.0-ff92c40-dirty
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: arm64
Essential: no
Depends: docker.io (>= 20.10.0), docker-compose-plugin (>= 2.0.0), curl, wget, systemd
Recommends: prometheus, grafana
Suggests: mosquitto-clients
Installed-Size: 50000
Maintainer: Home Automation Team <admin@home-automation.local>
Description: Smart Home Automation System for Raspberry Pi
 A comprehensive home automation system featuring:
 .
 * MQTT and Kafka message processing
 * TP-Link Tapo smart plug monitoring with KLAP protocol support
 * Prometheus metrics collection and Grafana dashboards
 * Multi-sensor support (temperature, humidity, motion, light)
 * Docker Compose orchestration
 * Raspberry Pi Pico WH firmware for wireless sensors
 * Energy monitoring and time-series visualization
 * Software Bill of Materials (SBOM) for security and compliance
 .
 This package installs the complete home automation stack with
 automatic service management, configuration templates, and
 comprehensive documentation. Includes SPDX and CycloneDX format
 SBOMs for vulnerability scanning and compliance requirements.
Homepage: https://github.com/johnpr01/home-automation
